title: I was born in Belfast, Ireland on 19th November 1991
I am 27 years young
My nickname “Mick”
My Professional Record is 11-0 (6 KOs)
My weight is 57Kg, Super Bantamweight
I am 5 feet 7 inches tall. (173 cm)
My reach is 69 inches. (175 cm)
My boxing stance is Orthodox/Southpaw
I was 7 years old when I started boxing
My favourite boxing hero is Sugar Ray Leonard
My family is my main motivation for success
My favourite part of competing is winning
I believe my biggest strength in boxing is my ability to adapt in any situation
My favourite song I listen to prior to competing is “You'll never beat the Irish” - Wolfe Tones
I love to train hard, constantly improve and becoming the best at my craft
My favourite song to walk out to on fight night is “Grace” - Jim McCann
I love movies, my favourite sports movie is “Rocky IV”
My favourite movie is “The Godfather Part II”
One thing I dislike about training is cutting weight
My favourite food to eat the night before a big fight is chicken, rice & veg
My favourite cheat food is pizza
My favourite place to compete is Madison Square Garden, The Mecca of Boxing
I love to train hard, constantly improve and becoming the best at my craft
My biggest achievement to date in boxing was back in October 2015, when I won the World Amateur Champion, Ireland's first ever male World Championship Gold Medal
My main goal in boxing is to become World Champion
